Bytes: 353
WITH_TIDY_CHECKS is designed for users to set as an environment variable. It is named similar to WITH_TIDY, WITH_TIDAY_FLAGS, WITH_STATIC_ANALYZER and WITH_SYNTAX_CHECK.
Current build environment variables usually don't have GLOBAL prefix, right?
WITH_TIDY_CHECKS is for clang-tidy's 'checks' list, while WITH_TIDY_FLAGS is for clang-tidy's other flags.

